<h1 id="tip-1-filling-out-a-website-form-via-the-command-line">Tip 1. Filling out a website form via the command line</h1>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">curl <span class="nt">-F</span> <span class="s2">"mail=nobody@nothing.com"</span> <span class="nt">-F</span> <span class="s2">"msg=Thanks"</span> http://givingsoup.org/
curl <span class="nt">-X</span> POST <span class="nt">-F</span> <span class="s2">"mail=nobody@nothing.com"</span> <span class="nt">-F</span> <span class="s2">"msg=Thanks"</span> http://givingsoup.org/
<span class="c"># cat data.txt #mail=nothing@all.com&amp;msg=Anything Message</span>
curl <span class="nt">--data</span> <span class="s2">"mail=iwanna@yoursoap.com&amp;msg=Nice"</span> http://givingsoup.org/
curl <span class="nt">-d</span> <span class="s2">"@data.txt"</span> <span class="nt">-X</span> POST http://givingsoup.org/</code></pre></figure>

<!-- RETANGULO LARGO 2 -->
